   <abstract>Map of Middle Tennessee showing the area designated for the Tennessee Maneuvers. Roads and highways are drawn with a legend showing the classification of each. The map details single structures across the area and includes the cities of Lebanon, Murfreesboro, Nashville, and the towns of Hartsville, Smithville, Gallatin, Lafayette, and Portland. The Cumberland and Caney Fork rivers are included as are a number of creeks.</abstract>
   <abstract>Between 1942 and 1944 a series of seven large-scale U.S. Army war games played out in what eventually comprised 21 Middle Tennessee counties. Some 850,000 soldiers spent time practicing for the ultimate invasion of Western Europe. The Army chose Middle Tennessee because its terrain resembled that of Belgium, France, and Germany. The Cumberland River simulated the Rhine, vital for a strike into Nazi Germany.</abstract>
